node.title: NT records first community transmission case of COVID-19
node.description: The Northern Territory's first ever case of COVID-19 community transmission will send Katherine into a lockdown and Greater Darwin into a lockout  for 72 hours as of midnight.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded its\u00a0first ever case of COVID-19 community transmission, prompting a three-day lockdown in the Katherine area from midnight.", "It follows an unvaccinated man in his 20s testing\u00a0positive\u00a0after spending time in the community in\u00a0Darwin's rural area and Katherine.", "Katherine\u00a0residents will only be permitted\u00a0to leave their homes for five reasons.", "The case also means\u00a0Greater Darwin, including Palmerston and the rural area, will enter the Territory's first \"lockout\"\u00a0for the next 72 hours.", "Under the lockout,\u00a0fully vaccinated people will be required to wear a mask when outdoors but can otherwise\u00a0continue life as normal.", "However, unvaccinated people will be subject to full lockdown restrictions, including only\u00a0being able\u00a0to leave their home for five reasons.\u00a0", "People in the lockout area, once inside, will not be permitted to leave other than for essential work or to fly interstate.", "Chief Minister Michael Gunner announced the new measures at an emergency press conference held about 10pm on Thursday.", "More to come."]
